<FIRST>r i PM-Turkey-Bus     04-21 0078</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Turkey-Bus,0080</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nine Killed, 24 Injured In Bus Plunge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SIVAS, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus plunged into a ravine near this
central city, killing at least nine people and injuring 24, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
   Anatolia said the bus was traveling at a high speed when it
skidded off the road Thursday and fell into the ravine near Sivas,
275 miles east of Ankara.
   Most of the injured were reportedly in serious condition,
Anatolia said.
</TEXT>
