<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--CoughMusic     04-21 0131</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Cough Music,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>No Coughing During the Symphony</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A cough drop maker and a local radio station are
teaming up to offer sweets for the suite.
   People attending the Detroit Symphony Orchestra's Chamber Series
concerts April 28 and April 30 will receive free boxes of Luden's
Wild Cherry Throat Drops.
   The giveaway is meant to prevent the coughing and
throat-clearing that often provides an irritating counterpoint to
the music on stage, according to Hershey Chocolate U.S.A. and
WQRS-FM, which announced the promotion Thursday.
   The packages will be labeled ``Luden's Rimsky-Korsa `Cough'
Drops'' in a play on the name of classical composer Nicholas
Rimsky-Korsakov.
   ``Let's just hope patrons open their throat drop boxes before or
after each musical selection or during the applause,'' WQRS
spokeswoman Lori Schmidt said.
</TEXT>
