<HEAD>Strong Earthquake In Siberia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake struck a remote, mountainous
area of central Siberia today, but there were no reports of
casualties or damage.
   The quake measured 8.9 on the 12-point Soviet scale, and its
epicenter was located in the mountains of southwestern Yakutia,
Tass said.
   An 8 point earthquake is considered ``destructive'' on the
Soviet scale, but the area is remote and seismographs in the
regional capital, Yakutsk, 2,700 miles east of Moscow, recorded the
quake at at only 2.3 points, Tass said.
   The Soviet news agency said it had received no reports of
injuries or damage from the temblor, which occurred this afternoon.
