<FIRST>r a PM-WomanAssaulted     04-21 0242</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Woman Assaulted,0247</SECOND>
<HEAD>Central Park Jogger Raped, Beaten</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pack of youths descended on Central Park,
attacking three people including a 28-year-old jogger who was raped
and beaten into unconsciousness, police said.
   The woman was found by passersby about 1:30 a.m. Thursday
bleeding badly, her skull fractured, wearing only a bra and
suffering from hypothermia, said Chief of Detectives Robert
Colangelo. She was hospitalized in critical condition today.
   Co-workers described the woman as a Wall Street investment
banker who worked long hours and regularly jogged alone at night.
   ``The youths were in the park, and this was a crime of
opportunity,'' said Colangelo. ``They saw the woman, and it was
spontaneous.''
   Nobody was arrested on rape charges, but five youths were
charged in an earlier attack and robbery of a man walking home
through the park, said a police spokesman, Detective Joseph
McConville. Police were searching for as many as seven others, all
between the ages of 13 and 15, Colangelo said.
   Colangelo said evidence indicated the woman fought desperately
against at least a dozen assailants. A bloodied rock which police
believe was used in the attack was found near the battered woman,
he said.
   He said police believe youngsters who knew each other but were
not in a gang arrived in the park around 10 p.m., bent on starting
trouble. They tossed rocks at a passing taxi and assaulted another
woman after the rape, he said.
</TEXT>
