<FIRST>r a AM-LotteryRecord     04-21 0318</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Lottery Record,0328</SECOND>
<HEAD>Pennsylvania's Super 7 Jackpot Guaranteed to Hit Record $70 Million</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ANITA C. HUSLIN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HARRISBURG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Pennsylvania Lottery's Super 7 jackpot
reached an estimated world record of $70 million on Friday, and was
expected to keep climbing through Wednesday's drawing, lottery
officials said.
   Lottery spokeswoman Terry Murphy said sales are booming; nearly
7 million tickets were sold Thursday and Friday. Lottery officials
will continue to update the value of the pot as sales continue, she
said.
   ``I'm having a hard time just saying $70 million now,'' she
said. ``I don't know where it's going to end up. We won't know that
until Thursday morning.''
   The total, estimated from sales figures, apparently broke a
1-week-old world record of $69.9 million set in Illinois on April
15. That was split by four ticket holders.
   The Super 7 jackpot was climbing to unprecedented heights
because no one has bought a winning ticket for six weeks, Ms.
Murphy said.
   If one person gets a ticket with seven of the 11 winning numbers
in the $70 million jackpot, he or she would receive $2.69 million a
year for 26 years.
   Prior to the Illinois record, the world record set last fall was
a $61.98 million jackpot split among buyers of three tickets in the
California lottery.
   Pennsylvania's own largest previous jackpot was $46 million in
the Super 7 game, won by a Hollidaysburg couple on Oct. 14, 1987.
   Lottery officials are urging players to buy tickets early to
avoid long lines at lottery retail outlets. Players also should
only buy as many tickets as they can afford, Ms. Murphy said.
   Alease Green, assistant manager of a Sheetz convenience store in
Harrisburg, said people have formed lines up and down the aisles of
the store, waiting to buy tickets.
   ``There's been a lot today,'' she said. ``There's going to be
lots more, too, I'm sure.''
</TEXT>
