shares of stock to employees and cut its corporate work force 14
percent to thwart a hostile takeover effort by a Toronto-based
investment bank.
   The doughnut giant announced the steps Thursday and said it
would fight any takeover bid by Kingsbridge Capital Group, a
subsidiary of Unicorp Canada Corp., which said it acquired a 6.6
percent stake and may seek control of the doughnut maker, which has
more than 1,700 stores worldwide.
</TEXT>
