<FIRST>r f BC-Carolco-DeLaurentiis     04-21 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Carolco-DeLaurentiis,0146</SECOND>
<HEAD>Carolco to Buy De Laurentiis for $25 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Carolco Pictures Inc., maker of the Rambo
movies, has agreed to buy bankrupt De Laurentiis Entertainment
Group Inc. for more than $25 million.
   The agreement has been approved by the De Laurentiis board and a
creditors committee appointed by U.S. Bankruptcy Court, the company
said Thursday.
   Carolco will pay more than $25 million for a De Laurentiis
studio in Wilmington, N.C., and a 350-movie library that includes
such titles as ``Crimes of the Heart'' and ``Serpico,'' as well as
an interest in the reorganized company.
   De Laurentiis Entertainment Group, founded by Italian director
Dino De Laurentiis, filed for federal bankruptcy protection from
its creditors under Chapter 11 of the federal bankruptcy law last
August.
   A reorganization plan must be approved by the bankruptcy court.
</TEXT>
