<FIRST>r f BC-SharonSteel     04-21 0174</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Sharon Steel,0182</SECOND>
<HEAD>New CEO For Steelmaker</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FARRELL, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sharon Steel Corp.'s executive vice
president has been appointed chief operating officer of the
financially troubled company.
   A bankruptcy court-appointed trustee on Thursday placed E.
Leonard Kern in charge of day-to-day operations at the company's
lone steel plant, located in Mercer County.
   Trustee William Agnew said Kern ``brings back to Sharon the
knowledge, skills and tenacity to assist the company in its quest
to complete a successful reorganization under Chapter 11.''
   Kern replaces Walter Sieckman, who was moved to vice chairman as
an adviser to Agnew.
   Agnew recently said Sharon's 1988 operating profit of $23.5
million is not enough to sustain a company of its size. ``It's
better than not having made anything, but it's not good enough to
make the company viable,'' he said.
   Sharon reported a net loss of $40 million for 1988. It lost
$19.6 million on operations in 1987 and $21.1 million in 1986.
   Kern joined Sharon Steel in 1969 as general superintendent of
iron and steel operations.
</TEXT>
