<FIRST>r f BC-GM-Perkins     04-21 0146</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-GM-Perkins,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Perkins Named General Manager</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   James C. Perkins was named general manager of
General Motors Corp.'s Chevrolet Division, succeeding retiring
executive Bob Burger.
   Perkins, who also will become a vice president, takes over as
Chevrolet's general manager May 1 when Burger, 64, retires. The
announcement was made Thursday.
   Perkins, 54, returned to GM earlier this year after four years
at Toyota Motors Sales, U.S.A. As senior vice president there,
Perkins was in charge of the company's new Lexus luxury car
division.
   Perkins joined GM in 1960 in the Chevrolet zone office in Dallas
and was named general sales manager for GM's Buick Division in
1982. When he returned to GM from Toyota, Perkins was named
assistant general manager for Chevrolet.
   Burger joined Chevrolet in 1949 and became a GM vice president
in 1977. He was named Chevrolet's general manager in 1984.
</TEXT>
