<HEAD>Mexico Begins Liquid Gas Exports</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pemex, the government oil monopoly, said
Thursday it has begun exporting 11,000 barrels a day of liquid gas
intended for household use.
   Production of the gas exceeded 14,800 barrels per day in 1988,
satisfying Mexican demand and enabling Pemex to export for the
first time, the company said.
   Pemex said its liquid gas is a mixture of 60 percent propane and
40 percent butane, derived from petrochemicals and crude oil
refining.
